17 Sec. 5. Report; Judicial Department. By January 1, 2026, the Judicial
18 Department shall submit a report to the Joint Standing Committee on Judiciary that
19 includes, at a minimum, the following information:
20 1. Statistics on the number of cases in which courts have appointed private attorneys
21 to provide indigent legal services pursuant to the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 4, section
22 1807, subsections 1 and 2, with detail on the number of cases involving criminal
23 defendants, including the number of those defendants who were incarcerated and the
24 number who were not incarcerated when the appointments were made; the number of child
25 protection proceedings in which private attorneys were appointed; and the number of cases
26 involving other indigent legal services in which appointments were made; and
27 2. Information on implementation of the commission's duty to compensate private
28 attorneys appointed by a court pursuant to the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 4, section
29 1807, subsections 1 and 2, including any recommendations for improving or repealing Title
30 4, section 1807.
31 The Joint Standing Committee on Judiciary may report out legislation related to the
32 report to the Second Regular Session of the 132nd Legislature.
